  "text": "Raveh et al. [CITATION_1] believed that in addition to the surface hardness, fatigue crack initiation was also a function of residual strains in the nitrided layers, crystallographic orientation of different phases, and segregation of alloying elements near the surface region. The fatigue crack initiation resistance decreased with TiN content of the compound layer and the surface hardness due to its brittle nature. Moreover, incorporation of Ar in the nitriding plasma also decreased the crack initiation resistance, possibly as a result of inducing microstrains in the nitrided layers.",
